# AICP v74 — Protocol Backlog (repo-backed)

> Scope: **protocol only** (Core + extensions + registries + schemas + fixtures + conformance + profiles + implementer guides).
> Out of scope: platform/enforcer implementations, chat UX, agent internals, hosted trust services.

This backlog translates consumer adoption needs into **protocol deliverables** that can be shipped in-repo:
- RFC/Docs (normative)
- Registries
- JSON Schemas
- Golden fixtures (JSONL transcripts)
- Conformance suites + runner checks
- Profiles (bundle suites)
- Implementer tooling/quickstarts (adapter skeletons, CI templates)
- Snapshot + release discipline

## Current shipped baseline (as of v74)
- Core: envelope, hash-chain, message_hash, signatures verify, CONTRACT_PROPOSE/ACCEPT, CONTEXT_AMEND, ATTEST_ACTION, RESOLVE_CONFLICT, ERROR.
- Extensions productized: CAPNEG, ENFORCEMENT, POLICY_EVAL, PARTICIPANTS, TOOL_GATING, IDENTITY_LC, DELEGATION, WORKFLOW_SYNC, DISPUTES, SECURITY_ALERTS, ALERTS, RESUME, OBJECT_RESYNC, DELEGATED_IDENTITY.
- Profiles shipped (experimental status): AICP-BASE, AICP-MEDIATED-BLOCKING, AICP-MEDIATED-BLOCKING-OPS, AICP-RECEPTION-CHAT, AICP-RESUMABLE-SESSIONS, AICP-DELEGATED-IDENTITY, AICP-WORKFLOW-ORCHESTRATION-DELEGATION.
- Snapshot discipline exists (manifest + validate gate).

